<title>PHILIPPINES: TARLAC WORKERS VOTE TO STRIKE.</title>
<headline>TARLAC WORKERS VOTE TO STRIKE.</headline>
<dateline>MANILA 1997-08-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>Workers of Central Azucarera de Tarlac have voted to strike, the sugar miller said on Wednesday.</p>
<p>The union conducted a strike vote last Friday. The workers were protesting against a retrenchment programme which had laid off more than 500 workers.</p>
<p>The company lawyer said the labour department had already called for a conciliation meeting between workers and the management.</p>
<p>&quot;It doesn't mean that the workers will strike immediately,&quot; lawyer Arcadio Lopez told Reuters.</p>
<p>The retrenchment is aimed to make the company competitive which has been encountered financial difficulties due to the prevailing sugar glut.</p>
<p>The company operates a 3,000-hectare sugar complex belonging to the family of former President Corazon Aquino.</p>
